Award-winning singer David was left hysterical over a welcome speech prepared by his PA, Israel DMW to welcome him to the 02 arena performance. The Personal Logistics Manager, in a video, is seen adorning traditional Benin attire with a bell to announce his boss’s appearance at the show. As he walks, he keeps ringing, acting as a town crier. According to him: “This is the day we have been waiting for. Watch out as my Oga is set to do what he knows how to do best. Sit back and enjoy yourself. God bless you all.”   PSG star Neymar attends The Batman premiere     Alaafin’s estranged Queen confirms surgery     Zlatan Ibile flaunts second baby, vows eight more   - Advertisement - After his short speech, the International and Diplomacy graduate bowed and left the supposed stage. As he walked away, he continues to ring the bell. On October 25, 2021, the DMW boss via his Instagram page announced that his third show at the O2 will hold on March 5, 2022. He wrote: “It is time! London You wanted it even bigger, you wanted it even better and on the 5th of March, 2022 we make the most beautiful movie ever! Santa says tickets go live on Friday! Let’s go!” Reacting to the video, Davido shared it on his Insta story alongside a screenshot of the WhatsApp message sent him by his PA and accompanied it with multiple laughing emojis.